summary: Normal wedding: a woman in a beautiful white gown walks down the aisle as her lover waits near the altar. They say their vows,...
body:
Normal wedding: a woman in a beautiful white gown walks down the aisle as her lover waits near the altar. They say their vows, exchange rings, and then take photos in front of beautifully lit arch of vividly green plants and string lights, holding bouquets of dusty pink roses and soft green heathery plants. The magic is then dispelled by the terrible song choices of the DJ.

My wedding: I show up in a beautiful wedding gown, barefoot with a rapier strapped across my back, walk into a clearing where my wife emerges from the trees, also in a beautiful white dress and with a hand-forged rapier. The three rows of invitees gasp as we face off, circling until we dart in, tension builds as the fight begins. The clash of swords is muffled by the trees, and as one of us corners the other and puts the thin blade under her chin, we look into each other’s eyes. The swords drop and we makeout against a tree for like five minutes. Then we each cut a thin slice in the other’s palm and mix our blood as we weave a complex harmony in Gaelic. I rip off part of my dress to bind her wound, and she does the same for me. We’re finally married, and now the wedding games can begin. The archery contest is first. All of our wedding photos look like this.
